    <!-- ── Privacy policy ── -->
    <string name="privacidad_titulo">PadelDart Privacy Policy</string>
    <string name="privacidad_texto">
        PRIVACY POLICY — PadelDart\n\n
        Last updated: January 2025\n\n
        1. DATA CONTROLLER\n
        PadelDart is a mobile application developed as a Final Degree Project (TFG)
        by Iker, a DAM student. Data is stored exclusively on the user\'s device
        (local SQLite database) and is never transmitted to external servers.\n\n
        2. DATA COLLECTED\n
        — First and last name\n
        — Email address (used as login identifier)\n
        — National ID (for registration identification only)\n
        — Postal address and postcode\n
        — Age\n
        — Profile photo (stored locally)\n
        — Padel level, position, province and favourite court\n
        — Dartboard preferences and payment method\n\n
        3. PURPOSE\n
        Data is used exclusively to:\n
        a) Manage user sessions within the app.\n
        b) Display the profile card in the side menu.\n
        c) Filter the notice board by province.\n
        d) Personalise the gaming experience (darts and padel).\n\n
        4. LEGAL BASIS\n
        Processing is based on the user\'s express consent,
        given by accepting this policy during registration (Art. 6.1.a GDPR).\n\n
        5. RETENTION\n
        Data remains on the device until the user uninstalls the app
        or explicitly requests deletion.\n\n
        6. USER RIGHTS\n
        Users may exercise their rights of access, rectification, erasure,
        portability and restriction by contacting the developer or
        uninstalling the app (which removes all data from the device).\n\n
        7. SECURITY\n
        Data is stored in the app\'s private database (SQLite),
        only accessible by PadelDart, with no internet connection and no cloud backup.\n\n
        8. MINORS\n
        The app is not intended for users under 14 years of age.
        If you are under that age, do not register without your legal guardian\'s consent.\n\n
        By accepting this policy you confirm having read and understood all of the above.
    </string>
